e-apps%5Bbot%5D/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greptile-apps%5Bbot%5D/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"<a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"P0\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p0.svg?v=9\" align=\"top\"></a> **[CRITICAL-JS-VIOLATION] Heap Allocation Г”ГҮГ¶ Jane Street Principle #1 (ALLOCATION IS A BUG)**\n\n`HashSet<string>` is a heap-allocated reference type. Its introduction as a class field allocates on strategy construction, and every call to `Add` / `Contains` can trigger internal array resizing and string equality comparisons that produce further allocations. If `_proxTagCache` is queried inside `OnBarUpdate` or any order-update callback (which the \"RMA sentinel draw object management\" comment strongly implies), this violates the zero-allocation hot-path mandate. The Jane Street Sentinel requires replacement with a struct-based, fixed-capacity alternative Г”ГҮГ¶ for example, a sorted `long[]` of FNV-1a hashes (matching the `ExecutionIdRing` pattern already used in this file), or a pre-allocated open-addressed hash table with no resizing. **This PR CANNOT be merged until the allocation is refactored.**\n\n<a href=\"https://chatgpt.com/codex/deeplink?prompt=IMPORTANT%3A%20Work%20in%20the%20repository%20%22mdasdispatch-hash%2Funiversal-or-strategy%22%20on%20the%20existing%20branch%20%22feature%2Fepic6-cicd-docs%22.%20Checkout%20that%20branch%20%E2%80%94%20do%20NOT%20create%20a%20new%20branch%20or%20open%20a%20new%20PR.%20Push%20your%20changes%20to%20%22feature%2Fepic6-cicd-docs%22.%0A%0AThis%20is%20a%20comment%20left%20during%20a%20code%20review.%0APath%3A%20src%2FV12_002.cs%0ALine%3A%20255-256%0A%0AComment%3A%0A**%5BCRITICAL-JS-VIOLATION%5D%20Heap%20Allocation%20%E2%80%94%20Jane%20Street%20Principle%20%231%20%28ALLOCATION%20IS%20A%20BUG%29**%0A%0A%60HashSet%3Cstring%3E%60%20is%20a%20heap-allocated%20reference%20type.%20Its%20introduction%20as%20a%20class%20field%20allocates%20on%20strategy%20construction%2C%20and%20every%20call%20to%20%60Add%60%20%2F%20%60Contains%60%20can%20trigger%20internal%20array%20resizing%20and%20string%20equality%20comparisons%20that%20produce%20further%20allocations.%20If%20%60_proxTagCache%60%20is%20queried%20inside%20%60OnBarUpdate%60%20or%20any%20order-update%20callback%20%28which%20the%20%22RMA%20sentinel%20draw%20object%20management%22%20comment%20strongly%20implies%29%2C%20this%20violates%20the%20zero-allocation%20hot-path%20mandate.%20The%20Jane%20Street%20Sentinel%20requires%20replacement%20with%20a%20struct-based%2C%20fixed-capacity%20alternative%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20a%20sorted%20%60long%5B%5D%60%20of%20FNV-1a%20hashes%20%28matching%20the%20%60ExecutionIdRing%60%20pattern%20already%20used%20in%20this%20file%29%2C%20or%20a%20pre-allocated%20open-addressed%20hash%20table%20with%20no%20resizing.%20**This%20PR%20CANNOT%20be%20merged%20until%20the%20allocation%20is%20refactored.**%0A%0AHow%20can%20I%20resolve%20this%3F%20If%20you%20propose%20a%20fix%2C%20please%20make%20it%20concise.\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInCodexDark.svg?v=3\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInCodex.svg?v=3\"><img alt=\"Fix in Codex\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInCodex.svg?v=3\" height=\"20\"></picture></a>","created_at":"2026-05-23T19:13:47Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T19:14:01Z","html_url":"https://github.com/mdasdispatch-hash/universal-or-strategy/pull/8#discussion_r3293361770","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mdasdispatch-hash/universal-or-strategy/pulls/8","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/mdasdispatch-hash/universal-or-strategy/pulls/comments/3293361770"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/mdasdispatch-hash/universal-or-strategy/pull/8#discussion_r